      • createUserGroup

        private void createUserGroup()
        Create a new User_Groups2 entity constructed from the fields in com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR.EditUserProfileRequest with the default user group.

        Cause a new User_Groups2 entity to be persisted to the database. The actual persist is performed by com.yardi.ejb.UserGroupsBean.persist().

      • createUserProfile

        private void createUserProfile()
        Create a new Full_User_Profile entity constructed from the fields in com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR.EditUserProfileRequest.

        A new User_Groups2 entity is also created as part of this transaction to ensure referential integrity between the USER_PROFILE and USER_GROUPS database tables.

        Feedback provided: YRD0000 process completed normally.

      • deleteUserProfile

        private void deleteUserProfile()
        The Full_User_Profile entity specified by com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR.EditUserProfileRequest will be deleted.

        The corresponding rows in the UNIQUE_TOKENS, SESSIONS_TABLE and USER_GROUPS database tables are also removed to ensure referential integrity

        Feedback provided: YRD0000 process completed normally.

      • findFullUserProfile

        private Full_User_Profile findFullUserProfile​(java.lang.String userId)
        Find the Full_User_Profile entity for the given user ID.

        This method delegates to com.yardi.ejb.UserProfileBean.findFullUserProfile() to find entities matching the given user ID.

        Parameters:
        userId - user ID to find
        Returns:
        Full_User_Profile entity that matched the given user ID. Returns null if the persistence context has no Full_User_Profile entity matching the given user ID and the USER_PROFILE database table does not have a row matching the given user ID.

      • findUserGroups

        private java.util.Vector<User_Groups2> findUserGroups​(java.lang.String userId)
        Find all groups the given user ID belongs to.

        This method delegates to com.yardi.ejb.UserGroupsBean.find2() to find entities matching the given user ID.

        Parameters:
        userId - specifies the User_Groups2 entities to find.
        Returns:
        Vector containing every group the user belongs to. The returned vector is empty if the persistence context has no User_Groups2 entity matching the given user ID and the USER_GROUPS database table has no rows matching the given user ID.

      • findUserProfile

        private void findUserProfile()
        Find the Full_User-Profile entity.

        The result of this find will determine whether the user can create, update, or delete. If the Full_User_Profile entity is found, update and delete are allowed. Create is allowed if the Full_User_Profile entity is not found.

        If the Full_User_Profile entity was found then mapFullUserProfile() is called to map the Full_User_Profile entity to com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR.EditUserProfileRequest which becomes part of the web response.

        Feedback provided: 

        YRD0000 process completed normally
YRD000D no such user name

      • findUserSessions

        private java.util.Vector<Full_Sessions_Table> findUserSessions​(java.lang.String userId)
        Find all sessions for the given user.

        This method delegates to com.yardi.ejb.SessionsTableBean.findFull_Sessions_Table() to find Full_Sessions_Table entities matching the given user ID.

        Parameters:
        userId - specifies the the Full_Sessions_Table entities to find.
        Returns:
        Vector containing all of the user's sessions. The returned vector is empty if the persistence context has no Full_Sessions_Table entity matching the given user ID and SESSIONS_TABLE database table has no rows for the given user ID.

      • findUserTokens

        Returns:

      • getFeedback

        public java.lang.String[] getFeedback()
        Returns the current feedback.

        Each operation, create, read, update and delete, sets the feedback field to indicate status of the operation. Clients call this method to determine the status of the most recent method called that provides feedback.

        Feedback has two parts, a message ID and a message description

        Specified by:
        getFeedback in interface EditUserProfileCTRL
        Returns:
        String[] containing the current feedback

      • handleRequest

        public void handleRequest()
        An abstraction to handle the request from the web.

        The client only needs to call this method after injecting the web request and initializing the web request. Based on the request, this method delegates to the appropriate method to complete the rest of the process.

        Specified by:
        handleRequest in interface EditUserProfileCTRL

      • inzEditRequest

        public void inzEditRequest()
        Directs the web request to initialize itself.

        There are two kinds of initialization, special and normal. Special initialization is performed for a find, delete or read request. Normal initialization is performed for every request.

        Specified by:
        inzEditRequest in interface EditUserProfileCTRL
